<li><a href="http://www.freebsd.org/doc/en_US.ISO8859-1/books/handbook/x-xdm.html" class="external text" title="http://www.freebsd.org/doc/en_US.ISO8859-1/books/handbook/x-xdm.html" rel="nofollow">The X Display Manager</a>, from the *<a href="http://www.freebsd.org/doc/en_US.ISO8859-1/books/handbook/" class="external text" title="http://www.freebsd.org/doc/en_US.ISO8859-1/books/handbook/" rel="nofollow">FreeBSD Handbook</a></li>
<li><a href="http://blogs.ittoolbox.com/linux/locutus/archives/linux-login-with-a-windows-box-and-xdmcp-15547" class="external text" title="http://blogs.ittoolbox.com/linux/locutus/archives/linux-login-with-a-windows-box-and-xdmcp-15547" rel="nofollow">Linux login with a Windows box and XDMCP</a> A guide to login to linux using windows.</li>
<li><a href="http://compsecblog.bruceblacklaws.com/2008/07/x-display-manager.html" class="external text" title="http://compsecblog.bruceblacklaws.com/2008/07/x-display-manager.html" rel="nofollow">GNU/Linux XDMCP video tutorial</a></li>
